      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variable-Length (Ragged) Batches"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "flash_attn_varlen_func"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " API processes a packed batch of sequences with different lengths without any padding, maximising GPU utilisation across a heterogeneous request batch:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import torch\nfrom flash_attn import flash_attn_varlen_func\n\ndef varlen_attention_example():\n    \"\"\"\n    Packed batch of 3 sequences with different lengths: [512, 1024, 768].\n    All sequences packed into a single 1D tensor; cu_seqlens marks the boundaries.\n    \"\"\"\n    H, d = 16, 128\n    device = \"cuda\"\n    dtype = torch.float16\n\n    seq_lens = [512, 1024, 768]\n    total_tokens = sum(seq_lens)  # 2304\n\n    # Pack all tokens into (total_tokens, H, d)\n    q = torch.randn(total_tokens, H, d, dtype=dtype, device=device)\n    k = torch.randn(total_tokens, H, d, dtype=dtype, device=device)\n    v = torch.randn(total_tokens, H, d, dtype=dtype, device=device)\n\n    # Cumulative sum gives sequence start/end offsets\n    cu_seqlens = torch.tensor([0, 512, 1536, 2304], dtype=torch.int32, device=device)\n    max_seqlen = max(seq_lens)  # 1024\n\n    out = flash_attn_varlen_func(\n        q, k, v,\n        cu_seqlens_q=cu_seqlens,\n        cu_seqlens_k=cu_seqlens,\n        max_seqlen_q=max_seqlen,\n        max_seqlen_k=max_seqlen,\n        causal=True,\n    )\n    # out.shape == (2304, H, d)  \u2014 same packed layout\n    return out"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FlashAttention-3: Asynchronous Pipelining on Hopper"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "H100 (Hopper) GPUs introduce new instructions that FA3 exploits:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "TMA (Tensor Memory Accelerator): "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "hardware-managed async bulk copies from HBM \u2192 SRAM, freeing compute cores from memory-management work."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "WGMMA (Warpgroup Matrix Multiply Accumulate): "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "128-thread warpgroup MMA instructions that achieve higher peak FLOP/s than standard WMMA on A100."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Warp specialization: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "different warps within a thread-block take different roles \u2014 \"producer\" warps issue TMA loads while \"consumer\" warps execute GEMM. This overlaps memory and compute latency within a single SM."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The result is that on H100 FP16, FA3 achieves approximately 75% of peak FLOP/s (740 TFLOP/s vs ~989 TFLOP/s theoretical), compared to FA2's ~35% on the same hardware:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# FlashAttention-3 is distributed as a separate package\n# pip install flash-attn-3  (or build from the hopper branch of the repo)\n# Currently (2024) requires: H100/H800, CUDA 12.3+, PyTorch 2.1+\n\ntry:\n    from flash_attn_interface import flash_attn_func as flash_attn3_func\n    FA3_AVAILABLE = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    FA3_AVAILABLE = False\n\nimport torch\nfrom flash_attn import flash_attn_func as flash_attn2_func\n\ndef run_attention(q, k, v, causal=True, prefer_fa3=True):\n    \"\"\"\n    Use FA3 if available and on Hopper, otherwise fall back to FA2.\n    q/k/v: (B, N, H, d), dtype float16 or bfloat16, on CUDA.\n    \"\"\"\n    is_hopper = torch.cuda.get_device_capability() >= (9, 0)\n    if prefer_fa3 and FA3_AVAILABLE and is_hopper:\n        return flash_attn3_func(q, k, v, causal=causal)\n    return flash_attn2_func(q, k, v, causal=causal)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FP8 Support in FA3"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FA3 adds FP8 (E4M3 format) for both Q/K/V inputs and the attention output, roughly halving memory bandwidth pressure versus FP16 and enabling larger effective batch sizes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# FP8 attention requires FA3 and H100\n# Scales (per-tensor or per-token) are required to map FP8 values to real magnitudes\n\nimport torch\ntry:\n    from flash_attn_interface import flash_attn_func_fp8\n    HAS_FP8 = True\nexcept ImportError:\n    HAS_FP8 = False\n\ndef fp8_attention_demo(B=1, N=2048, H=16, d=128):\n    if not HAS_FP8:\n        print(\"FA3 with FP8 not available on this system\")\n        return\n\n    device = \"cuda\"\n    # Cast to FP8 E4M3 (torch.float8_e4m3fn)\n    q_fp16 = torch.randn(B, N, H, d, dtype=torch.float16, device=device)\n    q_fp8 = q_fp16.to(torch.float8_e4m3fn)\n\n    k_fp16 = torch.randn(B, N, H, d, dtype=torch.float16, device=device)\n    k_fp8 = k_fp16.to(torch.float8_e4m3fn)\n\n    v_fp16 = torch.randn(B, N, H, d, dtype=torch.float16, device=device)\n    v_fp8 = v_fp16.to(torch.float8_e4m3fn)\n\n    # Per-tensor scale factors (actual values depend on calibration)\n    q_scale = q_fp16.abs().max() / 448.0   # 448 = max FP8 E4M3\n    k_scale = k_fp16.abs().max() / 448.0\n    v_scale = v_fp16.abs().max() / 448.0\n\n    out = flash_attn_func_fp8(\n        q_fp8, k_fp8, v_fp8,\n        q_scale=q_scale, k_scale=k_scale, v_scale=v_scale,\n        causal=True,\n    )\n    return out   # (B, N, H, d) in FP16"
          }
        ]
      },
