            "type": "text",
            "text": "Installation and Version Selection"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "bash"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# FA2 \u2014 stable, works on A10/A100/H100, Python 3.8+, CUDA 11.8+\npip install flash-attn --no-build-isolation\n# Verify: python -c \"import flash_attn; print(flash_attn.__version__)\"\n\n# FA3 \u2014 Hopper-only, experimental (as of 2024)\n# Either install from the hopper branch or wait for a stable release:\n# pip install flash-attn-3  (if published; check the release page)\n# Build from source:\n# git clone https://github.com/Dao-AILab/flash-attention --branch hopper\n# cd flash-attention && pip install -e \".[hopper]\" --no-build-isolation\n\n# In transformers-based code (HuggingFace):\n# model = AutoModel.from_pretrained(..., attn_implementation=\"flash_attention_2\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Most production users should use FA2. FA3 is worth targeting only if you are specifically deploying on H100 clusters and have validated the experimental API stability for your use case."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "FlashAttention-1 proved that IO-aware tiling eliminates the N\u00b2 memory bottleneck. FA2 fixed its parallelism and head-dimension limitations, added GQA/MQA support, and became the default attention implementation in nearly every production LLM serving stack. FA3 goes further by exploiting Hopper-specific async hardware to reach ~75% of H100 peak FP16 throughput and adds FP8 support. For most teams running on A100 or earlier, FA2 is the right choice; FA3 is a meaningful upgrade only on H100 hardware."
          }
        ]
      }
